          "text": "Here is a structured report of how **git-ai** at `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai` is organized and how checkpointing, change history, diffs, and the commit path fit together.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall project structure\n\n**Rust crate** (`Cargo.toml`): `git-ai` is a library + binary (`main.rs`, `lib.rs`) with heavy use of `serde`, `imara-diff`, async (`smol`/`futures`), and optional `git2`.\n\n**Top-level layout (conceptual):**\n\n| Area | Path | Role |\n|------|------|------|\n| Core library surface | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/lib.rs` | Re-exports `api`, `auth`, `authorship`, `commands`, `git`, `daemon`, `mdm`, `metrics`, etc. |\n| CLI / subcommands | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/commands/` | `checkpoint`, `blame`, `line_history`, hooks, `git_handlers`, etc. |\n| Authorship & working state | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/` | Working log, virtual attributions, post-commit, serialization, diff helpers |\n| Git integration | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/git/` | `repository`, `repo_storage`, refs, rewrite log, traversal |\n| Daemon / async checkpoint | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/daemon.rs` + `src/daemon/` | Family actors, checkpoint sequencing, can call `post_commit_with_final_state` |\n| IDE / agent installers | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/mdm/` | Hook installers, per-IDE agent configs |\n| Tests | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/tests/` | Integration tests, `line_mapping_tests.rs`, git-compat |\n| Agent/editor glue | `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/agent-support/` | VS Code, IntelliJ, OpenCode, Amp TypeScript helpers |\n\n**On-disk git-ai state (per repo)** under `.git/ai/` (from `RepoStorage` in `repo_storage.rs`): `working_logs/<base_commit_sha>/` holds `checkpoints.jsonl`, `blobs/<sha256>`, and `INITIAL`; plus `rewrite_log`, `logs/`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Checkpointing — what it is and which files matter\n\n**Concept:** A **checkpoint** is one snapshot of edits (per file: content hash, attributions, optional added/deleted line ranges) appended as JSON lines to `checkpoints.jsonl` for a **base commit** directory (`working_logs/<parent_sha>/`).\n\n**Primary definitions** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/working_log.rs`:\n\n- `WorkingLogEntry`: `file`, `blob_sha`, `attributions`, `line_attributions`, optional `added_line_ranges` / `deleted_line_ranges` (1-based inclusive tuples).\n- `Checkpoint`: `kind`, `diff` (combined hash of file paths + blob SHAs), `author`, `entries`, `timestamp`, optional `transcript` / `agent_id` / `line_stats` / `prompt_id`, etc.\n- `CheckpointKind`: `Human`, `AiAgent`, `AiTab`.\n- `CheckpointLineStats`: aggregate `additions` / `deletions` (+ SLOC variants).\n\n**Persistence** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/git/repo_storage.rs`:\n\n- `PersistedWorkingLog::append_checkpoint` reads all checkpoints, may strip `transcript` for storage, prunes old char-level attributions, writes `checkpoints.jsonl`.\n- `read_all_checkpoints`, `write_all_checkpoints`, `mutate_all_checkpoints`, blob helpers under `blobs/`.\n\n**Creation pipeline** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/commands/checkpoint.rs`:\n\n- `run` → `execute_resolved_checkpoint` → `get_checkpoint_entries` (parallel per file) → builds `Checkpoint`, `append_checkpoint`.\n- Computes per-file stats and ranges via `compute_file_line_stats` / `compute_line_change_ranges` (see section 6).\n\n**Agent-driven checkpoint metadata** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/commands/checkpoint_agent/` (`agent_presets.rs`, `mod.rs`, etc.): maps Cursor/Claude/etc. events to `CheckpointKind` and file lists.\n\n**Pre-commit human checkpoint** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/pre_commit.rs` calls `checkpoint::run` with `CheckpointKind::Human` and `is_pre_commit: true`.\n\n**Other references:** `daemon.rs` (async checkpoint append), `reset_hooks.rs`, `rebase_authorship.rs` (squash/rebase working-log handling), `commands/status.rs` (`CheckpointInfo`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. “Change history” object — definitions\n\nThere is no type named `ChangeHistory`; the serialized structure is **`AuthorshipMetadata.change_history`**: `Option<Vec<ChangeHistoryEntry>>`.\n\n**Definitions** — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/authorship_log_serialization.rs`:\n\n```23:70:/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/authorship_log_serialization.rs\n/// Per-file change detail within a single checkpoint.\n/// Line ranges use the same compact string format as the attestation section:\n/// a single line is `\"n\"`, a range is `\"n-m\"`.\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct FileChangeDetail {\n    pub added_lines: Vec<String>,\n    pub deleted_lines: Vec<String>,\n}\n\n/// One entry in the per-checkpoint change history stored in the authorship note\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct ChangeHistoryEntry {\n    pub timestamp: u64,\n    pub kind: String,\n    // ... conversation_id, agent_type, prompt_id, model, prompt_text ...\n    pub files: BTreeMap<String, FileChangeDetail>,\n    pub line_stats: CheckpointLineStats,\n}\n\n/// Metadata section that goes below the divider as JSON\n#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\npub struct AuthorshipMetadata {\n    // ...\n    pub change_history: Option<Vec<ChangeHistoryEntry>>,\n}\n```\n\n`format_line_range_tuple` turns `(start, end)` into `\"n\"` or `\"n-m\"` for storage in `FileChangeDetail`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How added/deleted lines are tracked\n\n**At checkpoint time (source of truth for ranges):**\n\n1. Diff **previous** vs **current** file text with `compute_line_changes` (`imara_diff`, Myers + `postprocess_lines`) — `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/imara_diff_utils.rs`.\n2. `compute_line_change_ranges` in `checkpoint.rs` walks `LineChange` stream and merges contiguous runs into:\n   - **added**: new-file line coordinates;\n   - **deleted**: old-file line coordinates.\n\n```1940:1996:/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/commands/checkpoint.rs\n/// Compute added/deleted line ranges from a diff.\n/// Returns (added_ranges, deleted_ranges) where ranges are 1-based inclusive (start, end).\n/// Added ranges are in new-content line coordinates; deleted ranges are in old-content coordinates.\nfn compute_line_change_ranges(\n    previous_content: &str,\n    current_content: &str,\n) -> (Vec<(u32, u32)>, Vec<(u32, u32)>) {\n    let changes = compute_line_changes(previous_content, current_content);\n    // ... merges into added/deleted vectors ...\n}\n```\n\nThose tuples are stored on `WorkingLogEntry` as `added_line_ranges` / `deleted_line_ranges` (`working_log.rs`).\n\n**Aggregate counts** (`CheckpointLineStats`): `compute_file_line_stats` counts insert/delete lines per file; `compute_line_stats` sums across files for `checkpoint.line_stats`.\n\n**Attribution (who owns which text)** is separate: `AttributionTracker` in `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/attribution_tracker.rs` updates char/line attributions across edits; **move detection** uses `/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/move_detection.rs` (`detect_moves`, `InsertedLine`, `DeletedLine`, `MoveMapping`) to carry metadata across moves.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Commit flow — when is change history created?\n\n**Checkpoints** are written **whenever a checkpoint runs** (AI hooks, `git-ai checkpoint`, human pre-commit, daemon), not at commit time.\n\n**Serialized `change_history` in the authorship git note** is built in **`post_commit`**, which runs **after** a successful commit (or equivalent rewrite event), not inside the checkpoint writer.\n\nFlow:\n\n1. **Pre-commit** (`pre_commit.rs`): optional human `checkpoint::run`.\n2. **Commit completes**; wrapper/hook runs **post-commit** (`commit_hooks.rs` → `commit_post_command_hook`).\n3. `Repository::handle_rewrite_log_event` appends to `rewrite_log` and calls `rewrite_authorship_if_needed` (`rebase_authorship.rs`).\n4. For `RewriteLogEvent::Commit`, that calls `post_commit::post_commit` with `base_commit` = parent and new `commit_sha`.\n\nInside `post_commit` (`post_commit.rs`):\n\n- Loads working log for **parent** SHA (`working_log_for_base_commit`).\n- Refreshes prompts/transcripts (`update_prompts_to_latest`).\n- Builds `VirtualAttributions` from the working log → **`AuthorshipLog`** (attestations + prompts).\n- **Then** constructs `change_history` by **iterating `parent_working_log` checkpoints** and mapping each `WorkingLogEntry`’s range tuples through `format_line_range_tuple` into `FileChangeDetail`, plus prompt text resolution.\n\n```171:252:/Users/Andrew/School/ReSeSS_Research/tool_testing/git-ai/src/authorship/post_commit.rs\n    // Build per-checkpoint change_history for research metrics\n    // ...\n    let change_history: Vec<crate::authorship::authorship_log_serialization::ChangeHistoryEntry> =\n        parent_working_log\n            .iter()\n            .map(|cp| {\n                // ... FileChangeDetail from entry.added_line_ranges / deleted_line_ranges ...\n                ChangeHistoryEntry {\n                    timestamp: cp.timestamp,\n                    kind: cp.kind.to_str(),\n                    // ...\n                    files,\n                    line_stats: cp.line_stats.clone(),\n                }\n            })\n            .collect();\n\n    if !change_history.is_empty() {\n        authorship_log.metadata.change_history = Some(change_history);\n    }\n```\n\nSo: **per-checkpoint line ranges and stats are recorded at checkpoint time**; **`ChangeHistoryEntry` is assembled and attached to the authorship note at commit (post-commit) time** from that working log.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Diff / line-mapping logic (exhaustive map)\n\n| Piece | File | Purpose |\n|------|------|--------|\n| Line diff (git-like) | `src/authorship/imara_diff_utils.rs` | `compute_line_changes`, `LineChange` / `LineChangeTag`, byte/slice `DiffOp` |\n| Range extraction for checkpoints | `src/commands/checkpoint.rs` | `compute_line_change_ranges`, `compute_file_line_stats`, `compute_line_stats` |\n| Attribution across edits | `src/authorship/attribution_tracker.rs` | `AttributionTracker`, move handling via `detect_moves` |\n| Move detection structs | `src/authorship/move_detection.rs` | `InsertedLine`, `DeletedLine`, `MoveMapping`, `detect_moves` |\n| Reverse mapping for CLI | `src/commands/line_history.rs` | `map_new_to_old`, `reconstruct_diff_ops`, `find_checkpoints_that_touched_line` — walks `change_history` to relate a line at HEAD to checkpoints (ported from tests) |\n| Tests | `tests/line_mapping_tests.rs` | Same interleaved op reconstruction + mapping properties |\n| Tree/tree diff (other) | `src/git/diff_tree_to_tree.rs` | Git tree-level diffs (separate from per-file checkpoint diff) |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Structs / enums quick index\n\n| Name | Location |\n|------|----------|\n| `Checkpoint`, `WorkingLogEntry`, `CheckpointLineStats`, `CheckpointKind`, `AgentId` | `authorship/working_log.rs` |\n| `ChangeHistoryEntry`, `FileChangeDetail`, `AuthorshipMetadata` | `authorship/authorship_log_serialization.rs` |\n| `LineChange`, `LineChangeTag`, `compute_line_changes` | `authorship/imara_diff_utils.rs` |\n| `PreparedCheckpointManifest`, `PreparedCheckpointFile`, … | `commands/checkpoint.rs` |\n| `PersistedWorkingLog`, `InitialAttributions` | `git/repo_storage.rs` |\n\n---\n\n## 8. “Full directory structure”\n\nThe repo contains thousands of files (including `.git`, `targe